  "chapter": {
    "number": 4,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "A Remnant in Zion"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "In that day seven women",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "will take hold of one man and say,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "“We will eat our own bread",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and provide our own clothes.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Just let us be called by your name.",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Take away our disgrace!”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "On that day the Branch of the LORD",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "will be beautiful and glorious,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and the fruit of the land",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "will be the pride and glory of Israel’s survivors.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Whoever remains in Zion",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and whoever is left in Jerusalem",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "will be called holy—",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "all in Jerusalem who are recorded among the living—",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "when the Lord has washed away",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the filth of the daughters of Zion",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and cleansed the bloodstains from the heart of Jerusalem",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "by a spirit of judgment and a spirit of fire.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Then the LORD will create over all of Mount Zion",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and over her assemblies",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "a cloud of smoke by day",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and a glowing flame of fire by night.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "For over all the glory",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "there will be a canopy,",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "a shelter to give shade",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "from the heat by day,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and a refuge and hiding place",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "from the storm and the rain.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "footnotes": []
